line_1: To pour his golden tide through all her gates,
line_2: Her peaceful shores, where busy commerce waits

line_1: To court thy pencil early at thy gates,
line_2: Ambition knocks, and fleeting Beauty waits;

line_1: Tho', cloath'd with sackcloth, Justice in the gates,
line_2: By wicked Elders chain'd, Redemption waits,

line_1: In vain the arts unfold their gates,
line_2: For there no stranger ever waits;

line_1: Approaching now the well defended gates,
line_2: Their lowly suit a stern repulse awaits;

line_1: Mourn ye young Gardens, ye unfinish't Gates,
line_2: Ye Green Inclosures and ye growing Sweets,

line_1: (A Solemn Council call'd) the brazen Gates
line_2: Unbar; the Gods assume their golden Seats:

line_1: Still Peace and Plenty deck my beauteous gates.
line_2: On Isis still each gift of Fortune waits,

line_1: Hark! the Gaul is at her gates.
And longs to open her obsequious Gates.
line_2: Whilst Ulme th' Approach of her Deliv'rer waits,

line_1: And pour'd destruction through her hundred gates;
line_2: Waved his proud banner o'er the Theban states,

line_1: Hang their old Trophies o'er the Garden gates,
line_2: Our Gen'rals now,  retir'd to their Estates,

line_1: While they stood shiv'ring at the Gates.
line_2: Keep his Nose warm and lick the Plates,

line_1: When lo! advancing from the hallowed gates
line_2: With awe that fearfully her doom awaits

line_1: A name familiar to thy gates,
line_2: Once more a son of SPENCER waits,
